---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="SEO for SaaS Companies — Meridian" description="Meridian builds organic content engines for SaaS — programmatic SEO, comparison pages, integration content, and full-funnel tracking from search to trial signup.">

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-b from-dark to-dark-card pt-32 pb-20 md:pb-28">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6">
      <p class="text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-accent mb-6">SEO for SaaS Companies</p>
      <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-7xl font-extrabold text-hero-text leading-[1.05] tracking-tight max-w-4xl">
        Organic that compounds.<br />Not just traffic.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-body-muted max-w-2xl leading-relaxed">
        SaaS SEO isn't blog posts. It's programmatic feature pages, comparison content, integration docs, and bottom-of-funnel articles that convert. We build the infrastructure that keeps producing — and track it all the way to trial signups.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-10 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
        <a href="/audit" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 bg-accent hover:bg-accent-hover text-white text-sm font-medium rounded-lg transition-colors">
          Get a free audit &rarr;
        </a>
        <a href="/contact" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 border border-dark-border text-body-muted hover:text-white hover:border-white/20 text-sm font-medium rounded-lg transition-colors">
          Talk to us
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why SaaS SEO is Different -->
  <section class="bg-white py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-[44px] font-semibold text-dark leading-tight mb-4">SaaS buyers Google their problems before they ever talk to sales.</h2>
      <p class="text-light-text text-lg max-w-3xl mb-16">That window — from problem-aware search to trial signup — is where organic SEO wins or loses. Most agencies treat SaaS like any other client. We don't.</p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-10">

        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-2xl p-8">
          <div class="text-3xl mb-4">🧩</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark mb-3">Programmatic SEO at Scale</h3>
          <p class="text-light-text leading-relaxed">Feature pages, use case pages, integration pages — built to a template, indexed at scale. "Best CRM for [industry]", "[Your tool] vs [Competitor]", "How to integrate [Tool] with [Tool]." These capture high-intent traffic no blog post can.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-2xl p-8">
          <div class="text-3xl mb-4">⚔️</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark mb-3">Comparison & Alternative Pages</h3>
          <p class="text-light-text leading-relaxed">"[Competitor] alternative" searches convert at 3-5x the rate of generic keywords. We research, build, and optimize these pages — and keep them fresh when competitors change their positioning or pricing.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-2xl p-8">
          <div class="text-3xl mb-4">🔻</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark mb-3">Bottom-of-Funnel Content First</h3>
          <p class="text-light-text leading-relaxed">Not vanity traffic. We start with problem-aware, solution-aware, and product-aware content — the searches that happen when someone is already close to a decision. Higher CAC from paid? Organic captures the same intent for free.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-2xl p-8">
          <div class="text-3xl mb-4">📊</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark mb-3">Content → Trial → Activation Tracking</h3>
          <p class="text-light-text leading-relaxed">We don't stop at "traffic went up." We connect GA4 organic sessions to trial signups and — where possible — to activation milestones. You see which content actually drives revenue, not just impressions.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-2xl p-8">
          <div class="text-3xl mb-4">⚙️</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark mb-3">Technical SEO for SaaS Products</h3>
          <p class="text-light-text leading-relaxed">Dynamic content, JavaScript-heavy apps, user-generated pages, API docs — SaaS products create crawlability challenges most agencies don't understand. We audit daily and fix what costs you indexability.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-2xl p-8">
          <div class="text-3xl mb-4">📉</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark mb-3">Reduce CAC Without Cutting Paid</h3>
          <p class="text-light-text leading-relaxed">Build an organic content engine alongside paid — so as CAC rises on Google Ads and Meta, you're not fully exposed. Organic compounds. Paid stops the second you stop paying. We build the asset that keeps paying.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What We Build -->
  <section class="bg-hero-text py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-[44px] font-semibold text-dark leading-tight mb-4 text-center">What we actually build for you</h2>
      <p class="text-light-text text-lg text-center mb-16">Not a monthly report. A running content infrastructure.</p>

      <div class="space-y-6 max-w-3xl mx-auto">

        <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
          <span class="text-accent font-bold text-lg mt-0.5">01</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-dark">Programmatic page templates</h3>
            <p class="text-light-text mt-1">Feature pages, integration pages, and comparison pages built to a scalable template — designed for both search engines and conversion.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
          <span class="text-accent font-bold text-lg mt-0.5">02</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-dark">Competitor intelligence</h3>
            <p class="text-light-text mt-1">Weekly monitoring of competitor content, positioning changes, and new pages targeting your keywords. You know what they're doing before it shows in rankings.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
          <span class="text-accent font-bold text-lg mt-0.5">03</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-dark">Content briefs tuned to your ICP</h3>
            <p class="text-light-text mt-1">Not generic keyword-stuffed outlines. Briefs that reflect your buyer's specific problem, their stage in the funnel, and what will actually make them click "start free trial."</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
          <span class="text-accent font-bold text-lg mt-0.5">04</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-dark">Technical SEO tailored for SaaS architecture</h3>
            <p class="text-light-text mt-1">Daily crawl of your public-facing marketing site. JS rendering issues, broken canonicals, thin pages, and indexability problems caught before Google catches them first.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
          <span class="text-accent font-bold text-lg mt-0.5">05</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-dark">Full-funnel attribution</h3>
            <p class="text-light-text mt-1">GA4 setup and reporting that connects organic landing page → session → trial signup → activation. Know which content pays for itself and which to double down on.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Social Proof / Trust Signal -->
  <section class="bg-white py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 text-center">
      <p class="text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-accent mb-6">How we work</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-[44px] font-semibold text-dark leading-tight mb-6 max-w-3xl mx-auto">Built for SaaS teams who don't have time to babysit an agency</h2>
      <p class="text-light-text text-lg max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-12">No weekly status calls. No vague deliverables. You get a running dashboard, a content pipeline, and a clear log of every action taken and what moved in search as a result.</p>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 text-left">
        <div class="bg-hero-text rounded-2xl p-8">
          <p class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-dark mb-2">Week 1</p>
          <p class="text-light-text">Full technical audit, ICP mapping, competitor content gap analysis, and keyword strategy. You know exactly where you stand.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-hero-text rounded-2xl p-8">
          <p class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-dark mb-2">Month 1</p>
          <p class="text-light-text">First comparison and alternative pages live. Content pipeline running. Technical issues resolved. Tracking connected.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-hero-text rounded-2xl p-8">
          <p class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-dark mb-2">Month 3+</p>
          <p class="text-light-text">Compounding organic traffic. CAC decreasing. Clear attribution from content to trial. You can see which pieces are working.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="bg-hero-text py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-[44px] font-semibold text-dark leading-tight mb-12">SaaS-specific questions</h2>
      <div class="space-y-10">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-dark mb-2">We're already doing paid — do we need SEO?</h3>
          <p class="text-light-text leading-relaxed">Paid and organic aren't alternatives — they're complements. Paid captures intent right now. Organic builds the asset that captures the same intent in six months for free. The risk is being 100% dependent on paid when CAC rises.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-dark mb-2">How long before we see results?</h3>
          <p class="text-light-text leading-relaxed">Technical fixes often show GSC movement within 30 days. Comparison and alternative pages — 60-90 days to start ranking. Full compounding effect is a 6-12 month story. We show you movement along the way, not just a promise at month 12.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-dark mb-2">Our product changes frequently — how do you keep content accurate?</h3>
          <p class="text-light-text leading-relaxed">We build a content update protocol into the engagement from day one. Product changelog review, quarterly content audits, and automated monitoring for pages that fall in rankings (often a sign content has gone stale).</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-dark mb-2">Can you work with our existing marketing team?</h3>
          <p class="text-light-text leading-relaxed">Yes. We typically plug in as the SEO infrastructure layer — your team focuses on brand, demand gen, and product marketing. We handle the systematic side: audits, content pipeline, technical fixes, tracking.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-dark mb-2">Do you publish directly to our CMS?</h3>
          <p class="text-light-text leading-relaxed">On our Authority tier, yes — we can publish directly to WordPress, Webflow, or any CMS with API access. On Growth, you get publish-ready drafts with exact formatting instructions. Nothing sits in a queue.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-dark to-dark-card py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-[44px] font-semibold text-hero-text leading-tight">Let's look at your organic gap.</h2>
      <p class="mt-6 text-body-muted text-lg max-w-xl mx-auto">Free audit. We'll show you what your competitors are ranking for that you're not, and where the fastest wins are.</p>
      <div class="mt-10 flex flex-wrap gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/audit" class="inline-flex items-center px-8 py-4 bg-accent hover:bg-accent-hover text-white font-medium rounded-lg transition-colors">
          Get a free SEO audit &rarr;
        </a>
        <a href="/contact" class="inline-flex items-center px-8 py-4 border border-white/20 text-body-muted hover:text-white hover:border-white/40 font-medium rounded-lg transition-colors">
          Talk to us first
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
